On Loyalty Day, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation reaffirming allegiance to the United States and its founding principles. He emphasized the importance of reflecting on the freedoms Americans hold dear and honoring the Constitution. The proclamation also recognized the sacrifices made by thousands of Americans who fought and died to protect the country's flag and preserve its values of hope and freedom. Trump called on Americans to observe Loyalty Day with appropriate ceremonies, including recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance, and for government officials to display the flag on all government buildings and grounds.